This park is small. They have many squirrels! I find that in Philly they don't have many in the smaller parks, for whatever reason. They also seem to have a small murder of crows roosting in a tree trunk. I love Corvids.  Across the street from this park is a courtyard, a pool, and playground where they play many sports, mostly soccer it seems. Keeps the kiddos busy for summer. As the park is small, the benches are kind of limited to sit on and not in great shape. It's still a clean park where people do minimal things like small BBQs (not sure we're allowed to) play mallet ball or whatever it's called, maybe picnic, ride a bike, Rollerblade, walk around with your lover, read a book (my favorite). So enjoy a jog around and sit down to watch the stars..whatever you like. I think it's safe enough but that's my experience thus far, as someone sorta new to the area.

It’s not a perfectly maintained park but it serves the neighborhood. It has a dog water station, a port a pottie, a free mulch pile, and a little free library. It doesn’t get the amount of visitors that Mifflin Square gets, but perhaps that’s why I prefer this park. You can also use the bathrooms at Sacks playground next door.
